<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 39 
                    Prime Minister Churchill to President Truman
                    
                    Sent by the United States Military Attaché, London,
                        via Army channels.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d39</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">39</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="39" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 39 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1" type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="to">Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d39fn1">Sent by the United States Military Attaché, London,
                        via Army channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-29">29th May
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>.
                    Personal and top secret. Number 58.</p>
                <p>Your 48.<note n="2" xml:id="d39fn2">
                        <ref target="#d37">document No. 37</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I have sent the following telegram to Premier <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <list>
                            <item>“1. Your message of May 27.<note n="3" xml:id="d39fn3">See <ref target="#d35fn1">document No. 35, footnote 1</ref>.</note> I
                                shall be very glad to meet you and President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> in what is left of Berlin in
                                the very near future. I hope this might take place about the middle
                                of June.</item>
                            <item>2. Have repeated this telegram to President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> who has informed me that
                                this point was raised in your talks with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName>. All good wishes. I am very
                                anxious to meet you soon.”<note n="4" xml:id="d39fn4">Cf. <hi rend="italic">
                                        <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName>’s
                                        Correspondence</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                                    361.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Prime</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
